Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Cannabis (marijuana) is not necessarily known to be toxic to sheep. That being said, any thing in excessive amounts can be toxic. In other words, the dose makes the poison. There is a case of alleged poisoning in sheep causing the ovine to appear to be psychopathic, but there is no scientific evidence of it.

The article does not tell us of any insecticides nor does it give it any clinical signs of the animals to try and determine what happened.

High altitude disease can kill animals. We do not know if this is the case here. Again there are no clinical signs listed in the article.

Perhaps we will know more when a necropsy is performed and there is some laboratory testing on the tissues of the animals. More information from knowledgeable sources would be greatly appreciated. - Mod.TG

Maps of India can be seen at http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/india/india-political-map.htm and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5873744,57095.]
